layout.p:
Columns: 1;
                                                  ruled lines: 37;
                                                  written lines: 37; Uniform layout. The writing stands a little below the ruled line.The mishnah of each chapter is not divided into small sections as in printed editions of the Talmud, but is given in entirety before the gemara begins. Each chapter of the Mishnah ends with the phrase: סליק פרקא, and a few words of the mishnah are repeated as a heading to the gemara that treats on that part.Each chapter of the Gemara ends with: הדרן עלך.Each tractate ends with: סליקא מסכת.Folios 23r, 71r are left blank due to the fact that folio 23 and 71 respectively begin fresh quires written by different hands from the portions which in each case precede them, so that a new scribe began a new tractate. The concluding portions of the preceding tractates have been left out.
